3.	Design a neural Network for classifying news wires (Multi class classification) using Reuters dataset.
Aim:
      To design and implement a Neural Network model for multi-class classification of news wires using the Reuters dataset, where each news article is classified into one of multiple topics.

Description:

The Reuters dataset is a benchmark dataset used for topic classification.
It contains news articles labeled into 46 different categories.
In this experiment:
•	News articles are represented as sequences of word indices.
•	Data is vectorized into fixed-length numeric vectors.
•	A neural network with Dense layers is designed.
•	ReLU activation is used in hidden layers.
•	Softmax activation is used in the output layer for multi-class classification.
•	The model is trained using the Adam optimizer and Categorical Cross-Entropy loss.

Program:

import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense
from tensorflow.keras.datasets import reuters
from tensorflow.keras.utils import to_categorical
import numpy as np
num_words = 10000
(x_train, y_train), (x_test, y_test) = reuters.load_data(num_words=num_words)
def vectorize_sequences(sequences, dimension=10000):
    results = np.zeros((len(sequences), dimension))
    for i, sequence in enumerate(sequences):
        results[i, sequence] = 1.0
    return results
x_train = vectorize_sequences(x_train, num_words)
x_test = vectorize_sequences(x_test, num_words)
y_train = to_categorical(y_train)
y_test = to_categorical(y_test)
model = Sequential()
model.add(Dense(64, activation='relu', input_shape=(num_words,)))
model.add(Dense(64, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(46, activation='softmax'))
model.compile(optimizer='adam',
              loss='categorical_crossentropy',
              metrics=['accuracy'])
model.fit(x_train, y_train, epochs=10, batch_size=512, validation_split=0.2)
loss, accuracy = model.evaluate(x_test, y_test)
print("Test Accuracy:", accuracy)

Result :

The neural network successfully classifies Reuters news articles into 46 different categories with an accuracy of approximately 75–80%.
